title: "satie-cross-modal: Biographically Anchored AI Translations of Erik Satie's Piano Works"
abstract: >-
  A cross-modal AI framework that translates piano works by Erik Satie into
  period-faithful visual artworks. Combines CLAP audio embeddings, low-level
  acoustic descriptors via librosa, a handcrafted lexical bridge over four
  perceptual dimensions (palette, rhythm, surface, mood), and Stable
  Diffusion XL with IP-Adapter conditioned on curated fin-de-siècle
  Parisian visual references. Each piece is anchored to an editorial
  biographical phrase that situates the score within a moment of the
  composer's life. Released as the computational companion to the paper
  "Sonorous Brushstrokes".
